# Build artifacts and third-party dependencies should never be in the
# security-scan baseline — vulnerabilities in node_modules are tracked by
# the dependency audit (osv-scanner), not SAST, and minified third-party
# bundles in build outputs (e.g. shaka-player in expo's web-dist) trigger
# coincidental regex matches against credential-detection rules. Keeping
# these out of scope makes the SAST baseline meaningful — every finding
# that surfaces is either real, in our code, or a known false positive
# explicitly suppressed at the source line with `nosemgrep:<rule-id>`.

# JS / TS dependencies
node_modules/
**/node_modules/

# Build outputs
**/dist/
**/build/
**/.next/
**/web-dist/
**/web-build/
**/.expo/

# Source maps and minified bundles
**/*.min.js
**/*.bundle.js
**/*.map

# TypeScript build info
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Test snapshots and coverage
**/coverage/
**/__snapshots__/

# Local logs and artifacts
.local/logs/
/tmp/
